# Valgrind suppressions for `ctest -T memcheck` (see Halide_ENABLE_MEMCHECK and
# the `valgrind` CMake preset), which reruns every correctness test under
# valgrind.
#
# This file starts empty. The default memcheck options do not enable full leak
# checking, so the one-time LLVM ORC-JIT allocations that Halide's JIT triggers
# are not reported. Add entries here if you widen the options (e.g. add
# `--leak-check=full`) and need to silence errors originating outside Halide's
# own code (LLVM, the C++ runtime, or a GPU/driver stack).
